  <section id="introduction">
    <h2>1. Introduction</h2>
    <p>Peripheral devices are the backbone of human-computer interaction, bridging the gap between technology and functionality. These external devices help computers perform various tasks efficiently, from capturing input to displaying processed data. Let's explore how these devices revolutionize computing!</p>
    <img src="flowchart.png" alt="Peripheral Interaction Flowchart">
  </section>

  <section id="classification">
    <h2>2. Classification of Peripheral Devices</h2>
    <button class="collapsible">Click to Expand/Collapse</button>
    <div class="content">
      <p>Peripheral devices are classified into three main categories:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><b>Input Devices:</b> Provide data to the computer (e.g., keyboard, mouse).</li>
        <li><b>Output Devices:</b> Display or output processed data (e.g., monitor, speakers).</li>
        <li><b>Storage Devices:</b> Save and retrieve data (e.g., HDDs, SSDs).</li>
      </ul>
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>Category</th>
            <th>Examples</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td>Input Devices</td>
            <td>Keyboard, Mouse, Scanner</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Output Devices</td>
            <td>Monitor, Printer, Speaker</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Storage Devices</td>
            <td>HDD, SSD, USB Drives</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="input-devices">
    <h2>3. Input Devices</h2>
    <p>Input devices allow users to interact with computers. These devices capture data and send it to the processor for further action.</p>
    <ul>
      <li><b>Keyboard:</b> Variants include mechanical, ergonomic, and virtual keyboards.</li>
      <li><b>Mouse:</b> Optical and trackball mice enable efficient navigation.</li>
      <li><b>Scanners:</b> Convert physical documents into digital format.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section id="output-devices">
    <h2>4. Output Devices</h2>
    <p>Output devices make information accessible by displaying or producing it in a user-friendly format. Examples include:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><b>Monitor:</b> Display images, videos, and applications in real-time.</li>
      <li><b>Printers:</b> Produce physical copies of digital files.</li>
      <li><b>Speakers:</b> Generate audio for multimedia applications.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section id="storage-devices">
    <h2>5. Storage Devices</h2>
    <p>Storage devices play a crucial role in saving, retrieving, and securing data.</p>
    <ul>
      <li><b>HDD:</b> Traditional hard drives with large capacities.</li>
      <li><b>SSD:</b> Faster, more reliable solid-state drives.</li>
      <li><b>USB Drives:</b> Compact and portable storage solutions.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section id="trends">
    <h2>6. Emerging Trends in Peripheral Devices</h2>
    <p>Technological advancements are transforming peripheral devices:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><b>Virtual Reality (VR):</b> Immersive experiences with headsets like Oculus Quest.</li>
      <li><b>Wearables:</b> Smartwatches and fitness trackers for convenience.</li>
      <li><b>Biometrics:</b> Fingerprint and retina scanners for enhanced security.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section id="conclusion">
    <h2>7. Conclusion</h2>
    <p>Peripheral devices form the foundation of modern computing by enhancing interaction, accessibility, and performance. As innovation progresses, these devices will continue shaping the future of technology.</p>
  </section>

